parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TPS sensor can cause the engine to stall or cut out without warning, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when riding at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The engine stalls or cuts out without warning
hesitates
or backfires; the motorcycle loses power
especially when shifting gears or decelerating; the engine idles low and stalls out; the bike may not start immediately after stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rotor and stator can cause the engine to stall or cut out without warning, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when riding at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The engine stalls or cuts out without warning
the battery dies
the charging system fails
magnets are found in the oil strainer
the rotor assembly is destroyed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected engine shutdown or stalling can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially when riding at high speeds or navigating turns.
symptoms: The engine cuts out
surges
or stalls
often at idle or when letting off the gas
causing the RPMs to drop significantly; the motorcycle may die totally or lurch
leading to a loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Power Loss and Ticking Noise
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of power and unusual ticking noise can cause the motorcycle to stall or lose control, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The motorcycle loses considerable power
starts ticking loudly
and may stall or shut down
often at high speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TPS can cause the engine to stall or die, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine stalls or dies when the clutch is pulled in
the engine idles rough
the engine RPM drops to around 500 RPM
the engine surges
the rear wheel locks up when the bike dies with the clutch out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent engine stalling can cause loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine stalls when coming to a stop
the engine stalls when the clutch is pulled in
the engine surges
the engine RPM drops to around 500 RPM
the engine idles rough.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the carburetor mounting can cause the engine to lose power, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The carburetor pops out of its mounting
the engine loses power
the bike crashes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TPS can cause the engine to lose power, stall, or shut off suddenly, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine loses power
stalls
or shuts off suddenly
the engine idles down to a low RPM and then shuts off
the engine sounds rough and uneven
the bike jerks or hesitates when accelerating
the bike requires constant throttle input to stay running.
